        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Tuesday.<lb/></p>
            <p>Moorestown&#44; Burlington Co.<lb/>
                N. J.<lb/>
                July&#45;90.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Mr Morais.<lb/></p>
            <p>Your note reached<lb/> me with enclosed yesterday<lb/> morning through my nieces&#45;&#45;<lb/> &#38; thank you very kindly<lb/> for the clear idea you give me<lb/> of the &#39;Epithalamium&#39; and the &#34;Eco&#34;<lb/> article&#45;&#45;I feel that it must<lb/> have been quite a labor.<lb/></p>
            <p>Possibly because it is in such<lb/> contrast to our common&#45;place&#44;<lb/> matter&#45;of&#45;fact customs&#44; but&#44; for the<lb/> occasion&#44; I like the idea of all this<lb/> poetry &#38; sentiment and with all<lb/> due deference to your difference<lb/> of opinion&#44; I fancy that in the<lb/> musical language of the<lb/> original&#44; all this flowery flight&#44;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>style and tone are in exquisite<lb/> harmony and refined taste.<lb/></p>
            <p>Hoping that you may<lb/> not be suffering with the<lb/> heat&#44; and that the balance<lb/> of the summer may pass<lb/> comfortably with you&#44;<lb/> thanking you again for<lb/> your kindness believe me<lb/> Yours very truly<lb/> E. Berneisler.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
